To find the "turning point" (the peak) for experience, we look at the part of the equation where the effect of experience transitions from positive to negative.

For a quadritic eq $y = \beta_1 x + \beta_2 x^2$, the turning point occurs at:

$$
x^* = - \frac{\beta_{exper}}{2 \cdot \beta_{expersq}}
$$

Using our Regression coefficients:

* $\beta_{exper}=0.408$
* $\beta_{expersq}=-0.0006$

$$
x^* = - \frac{0.0408}{2\cdot(-0.0006)}
$$

$$
x^* = 34 \ text{years}
$$

